node.text:
Our very own Seren (@serencooks) walks us through how to make her Cuban-inspired swerve on everyone’s favourite French sandwich, the croque madame. Aromatic slices of mojo pork, a smoky jalapeño cheese sauce, salsa, pickles, chives (and bread and a runny egg of course). It looks absolutely BEAUTIFUL. Thanks Seren, see you at the World Cup!

NO VOTING THIS TIME, JUST SANDWICH GOALS! KEEP YOUR EYES PEELED FOR UPDATES ON THE FINAL!

node.text:
To celebrate the Tokyo Olympics starting today - where over 200 national teams will compete - Twisted chef, @hughwoodward, has cooked up his favourite fusion recipe! Flavours from across the continents combine in these delicious Crispy Hoisin Duck Chimichangas, a dish that would leave both China and Mexico winning gold. This recipe, along with loads more mouth-watering fusion dishes like Halloumi Saag and Banh Mi Sausage Rolls are available in Twisted: A Cookbook. Taste the world’s flavours from the comfort of your sofa, all while watching the greatest athletes on earth. Ready, set, go! (Link in bio) 

#Olympics #fusioncooking #summereats

Million Dollar Cheesy Taco Pasta
•

INGREDIENTS
700g beef mince
2 tbsp taco seasoning
1 cup diced peppers
1 cup diced onion
1/2 cup pickled jalapenos
1 cup grated cheddar
crushed nachos, to serve
2/3 cup cream cheese
Penne, cooked
2 tins chopped tomatoes 
•

CREAMY NACHO SCALLOPED POTATOES

INGREDIENTS
1 kg potatoes
3 tbsp melted butter
2 tbsp sea salt
5 tbsp cajun spice
500ml double cream
2 cloves garlic, minced
1 tbsp oil
3 mixed peppers, sliced
1 onion
500g beef mince
2 tbsp tomato puree
200g passata
200g Red Cheddar
Chopped tomatoes
2 chopped jalapeños
Spring onions
•
